title: For Sale/Trade:  Custom M91/30 w/ammo and accessories(reduced, sold some ammo)
postcontent:
I have an Izhevsk M91/30 that I sporterized for hunting, but am having trouble using it due to neck and shoulder issues. Therefore, I am selling it along with all my 7.62x54r ammo and accessories. 

First, my rifle; 1943 refurbed Izhevsk M91/30 that is a smooth operating good shooting rifle. The following modifications have been performed by me. I have about 6 years gunsmithing experience doing this kind of work so all is 'professionally' done.
The rear sight base was removed and a weaver/picatinney rail($10 value) drilled and tapped onto the dovetail part of the barrel. 
Then having a new AIM Sport 2-7x42 LER 30mm scope w/rangefinder reticle installed($70 value). It has been laser bore-sighted, but I have not had a chance to get to the range to fine tune it yet. 
Barrel has been cut and re-crowned to 20.25' then the OD turned down and threaded to accept an M14-1LH Muzzle Brake from CNC Warrior called 'The Russian Original'($30 value w/washer). It looks similar to the Draganov MB. The MB has been installed with a crush washer and blue loc-tite for a secure and properly timed installation. Total barrel length is 22.5'
Original stock has been modified with the front cut back and a UTG SWAT Tactical BP78 bipod installed along with QD sling swivels and padded sling(Bipod $30, QD swivels $10, Sling $15). 
On the butt, I cut the end down then added a Limbsaver type recoil pad($20) to maintain the original overall length. I used part of the lower front part of the stock as a cheek piece and put on a 9 round butt stock ammo sleeve($5). (see the pic)

Along with the set up I have 10 Izhevsk stamped surplus stripper clips in excellent condition.($10-$15 value) 
As well as 2 MOLLE II single grenade pouches in ACU camo that work really well as belt pouches for toting ammo. Each pouch will hold 5 loaded clips for a total of 50 rounds in the 2 pouches. Great for hunting.($5-$8 value)

For the Ammo;($60-$85 value depending on where you get it)
40 rounds of PRVI Partisan PPU 150gr SP brass cased, boxer primed reloadable hunting ammo.($30-$40)
59 rounds of Yugoslavian M30 Brass cased Berdan primed corrosive surplus ammo. The next best thing to the 7N1 Sniper ammo.($30-$45 value)

I will sell some of the ammo separately. See my other listing on which and how much.

Taking the low side values, which I feel are a good fair value in today's market(tried to base values from going online pricing), That puts the rifle at $275. If you take the value on the parts I installed($190) that puts the rifle itself at $85. That does not take into consideration any of my time and labor. All in all I think it is a very fair price for what you are getting so, suffice it to say, my price is firm.

Call or text eight16-255-767eight or hit the contact seller button. If emailing please give your name and a number so I can call you back or I will not respond. Thanks for looking

Pistol approximately 10 months old. Only 150 high quality rounds fired at the range. Includes all original case candy plus (2) 15 round mags. Unfortunately NO TRADES at this time.

HK INFO
A recent HK pistol design, the P30 is a modern police and security pistol that combines function and safety. Ergonomic features include a special grip frame with interchangeable backstrap inserts and lateral plates, allowing the pistol to be individually adapted to any user. Ambidextrous controls include dual slide releases and magazine release levers.

Variants with a conventional double-action/single action trigger have a serrated decocking button located on the rear of the frame. Variants with HK’s enhanced double action only Law Enforcement Modification* (LEM) trigger have no external decocking controls. 

The HK Law Enforcement Modification (LEM) trigger system combines the advantages of a cocked striker component (constant level of trigger pull from first to last round fired) with a double-action hammer system. Using such an enhanced trigger system consolidates ease of use and safety into a convenient, innovative trigger operation—one that reduces the chance of unintended firing. And in case of an ammunition-related failure to fire, all that is needed is an additional second or third squeeze of the trigger without the need of first pulling the slide back to re-cock the pistol. The enhanced LEM trigger system combines the reliability of a double action revolver trigger with the crisp trigger of a single action pistol.

A Picatinny rail molded into the front of the frame makes mounting lights, laser aimers, or other accessories easy and convenient. The extractor doubles as a loaded chamber indicator providing a subtle tactile and visual reminder of a loaded chamber.

Extensively tested, the P30 has already been adopted by several European police agencies. Excellent weight and balance make the P30 naturally pointable, easy to control, and accurate to shoot. An open notch rear sight with luminous (non-radioactive) contrast points allows for fast and accurate target acquisition, even under poor lighting conditions.

During a recent (2009-2010) endurance test, a P30 test pistol fired more than 91,000 rounds without any major component failures.

Key Features:
•Special grip frame with interchangeable backstrap inserts and lateral plates
•MIL-STD-1913 (Picatinny) rail on frame for mounting lights and accessories
• Corrosion proof fiber-reinforced polymer frame
•Polygonal bore profile for increased velocity, easier cleaning, and longer barrel life
• Patented HK recoil reduction system
•One piece machined slide made from nitro-carburized steel
•Corrosion resistant “hostile environment” blued finish
• Ambidextrous slide levers and
•Ambidextrous magazine release magazine
•Patented lock-out safety device
•Bobbed hammer (LEM models)
• Automatic hammer and firing pin safeties

To get updates of our new arrivals, "like" our Facebook page, and visit www.freerepublicfirearms.com for more information. If you contact us via email, please include your name and phone number to eliminate spammers and to ensure we can contact you. Occasionally we have problems with messages from hidden email addresses that are sent through gun listing/auction sites. Our reply emails are being returned as undeliverable, so if we don't respond to your email, please make sure we have another way to contact you.  We do not hold firearms, magazines, and accessories, because people do not always follow through with the purchase. Items are sold on a first come; first serve basis.

Trades:
We will consider trades from local, in-person buyers, but we cannot give a value on a gun unless we see it in person. Most of our firearms are new, and we are very selective about what used firearms we sell.   Please realize will cannot pay full retail for your firearm. We are a business, and there has to be room for us to make a small amount when we resell the firearm.  Let us know what you have to trade, and we will let you know if it is something we need.  If you are an out of state buyer, we will not consider a trade. 

About us:
Free Republic Firearms is a family owned FFL dealer located in Massillon Ohio. We are dedicated to supplying quality firearms, ammunition, and accessories to responsible gun owners for the purposes of self-defense, recreation, hunting, shooting sports, and collections.

We seek to make products affordable for our customers by stocking products that our customers need, rather than incur the costs of huge inventories, and large payrolls. Unlike large retailers, we keep our costs low by using our suppliers’ inventories to supplement our inventory. We bring additional products into our inventory as our customers need them, and pass on the savings of our low overhead costs to you.

We believe in providing firearms to responsible people who understand the importance of the 2nd Amendment, and the responsibility we have to protect it.  We are not interested in supplying firearms to those in society who do not have the morals, maturity, and character to be responsible gun owners.  It is our right to refuse to sell firearms to any person. We are interested in arming responsible citizens so that they can defend themselves against the criminal element, not arming the criminal element of society.

Extra information:
To all the spammers and criminals that can't legally buy guns, don't contact us asking to meet in a parking lot to complete a cash sale, or to trade a stolen laptop or other electronics for our guns. You shouldn't have guns, and we're definitely not going to help you get one.  To those who are under the legal age to buy firearms or handguns, we understand your desire to have a gun, but we will not break the law to sell you one, so please don't ask. We believe that if an 18 year old is old enough to fight for our country in the armed forces, they should be able to buy a gun. But until a little common sense is used in Washington DC, we cannot sell handguns to anyone under 21, and long guns to anyone under 18.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Czechpoint VZ-58 Folder 7.62x39 w/ ammo
postcontent:
Has 4 years left on its 5 year transferable warranty. Czechpoint is still backordered for months. Round count is very low (~300). Runs perfectly with all the ammo I tried (Tula, Wolf, GT). 

Vz58 aren't aks. They are much smaller, lighter, softer shooting than a stamped AK but built on a stronger milled receiver and can be fed with stripper clips due to open top design. The czechs know their firearms and told the ussr pre cold war that they would not be converting to the ak47. The vz design was originally designed for a larger battle rifle round but shrunk to accomodate the ussr's desire for 7.62x39.

Gun has a nice smooth trigger. Stock can be worked one handed unlike ACE folders which need you to jam your pistol grip into your gut to get more leverage. Has the lacquered finish Waffen Works is known for. Added a lot of extras to the gun. 

VZ-58. Chambered in 7.62. Distributed by Czechpoint USA, originally converted by Waffen Works.
